
firstly we need to install the tool OPENLENS on our labtop
- CLICK on the install app and open
- click on browse cluster in catalog  to open it
- NB for any thing to have access to our cluster it most have had access to the config file ie ~/.kube/config
- click on cluster on the left conner
- on labels , click on the config file below , this will connect u to ur cluster
- when u eventually get in the cluster , on the left conner u will see  NODES, WORKLOADS, CONFIG, NETWORK, STORAGE, NAMESPACE, EVENT, HELM, ACESS CONTROL
-  TO SEE ur node clicke on node, 
- to describe ur node click on the node name u want it to describe and it will open u a describtion of that node